fields.name: Hypar
fields.description:
Hypar is the next-generation platform for designing buildings and building systems.

Systems on Hypar can be easily connected and shared, so spinning up a new project is a snap. With connections to Revit, Rhino, Grasshopper, and Excel, Hypar makes it easy to bring automation to your existing workflows and projects. Quickly perform feasibility studies and schematic designs, or build and customize your own interactive product to share with customers or clients.

Hypar is a flexible, extensible platform built on open standards and frameworks, which means you can easily add your own intelligence, in the form of C# code, Grasshopper scripts, or Excel spreadsheets. Leverage the lightweight, open source Elements library to work with BIM objects and geometry in a modern, cloud-native way.

opengraph_data.title: Higharc Raises $21 Million Series A Led by Spark Capital
opengraph_data.description: Higharc, the all-in-one homebuilding platform for design, sales, and construction, announced today that it has raised $21 million in Series A funding, led by Spark Capital. New investors include MetaProp, Montage Ventures, Tectonic Capital, PlanGrid Co-Founder Ralph Gootee, Built Technologies Founder Chase Gilbert and Carta CTO Jerry Talton. Existing investors Pillar Ventures, Javelin Venture Partners, Lux Capital and Vertex Ventures also participated in the round. Higharc will use the capital to expand and scale its current offering to meet the growing demand for solution-based software in the industry. Additionally, funding will support expansion of its sales, customer success and engineering teams.
